Sinha, son of former union finance minister Yashwant Sinha, is the sitting MP of Hazaribagh. Sinha was conspicuous by his absence during polling in Hazaribag constituency on Monday.
title: BJP show-causes sitting MP Jayant Sinha for skipping campaigning
Trump sparks outrage with 'unified Reich' post in Truth Social video

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, BSE Sensex and Nifty50, opened in red on Tuesday. While BSE Sensex dipped over 100 points, Nifty50 was down over 15 points.
title: BSE Sensex opens over 100 points down; Nifty50 near 22,475

description: Wasim Akram has warned Sunrisers Hyderabad about the formidable bowling attack of Kolkata Knight Riders before their IPL 2024 Qualifier 1 match. KKR finished the league stage with a net run rate of 1.428, showcasing dominance in both batting and bowling. Akram praised KKR's collective effort throughout the season, emphasizing their ability to consistently take wickets.
title: IPL Qualifier 1: Why ex-Pak legend favours KKR against SRH
Aircraft flies into flock of flamingos, at least 40 birds dead

description: Temperatures remained above 45 degrees Celsius in large parts of Rajasthan, Haryana, Delhi, Chandigarh and Uttar Pradesh, affecting daily life as many chose to remain indoors in the afternoon. The crippling heat strained low-income households, which often have poor access to water and cooling, and tested the endurance of outdoor workers toiling in the searing sun, forcing them to take frequent breaks.
title: Parts of north India reel under severe heatwave conditions

description: Twenty-one sailors aboard the Dali ship are enduring severe hardships as they remain stranded at sea. The vessel has been immobilized for an extended period due to mechanical issues, placing the crew in a precarious situation without access to essential resources. The ordeal began when the Dali ship encountered mechanical problems that halted its journey, leaving it adrift and unable to reach a safe harbor.
title: 'Getting worse': 20 Indians on board facing ‘tough’ time on Dali

description: Vishal Agarwal, father of minor accused in Pune Porsche crash case, detained in Maharashtra's Sambajinagar by police. Minor held for rash driving causing two deaths in Kalyaninagar. Pune Police seek permission to try minor as adult under Juvenile Justice Act. Incident treated seriously, action taken under section 304 of IPC for heinous crime.
title: Pune Porsche accident: On the run, drunk teen driver's father held from Aurangabad

description: Former Pakistan captain Wasim Akram expressed disappointment over England players' absence from the Indian Premier League 2024 playoffs due to national commitments. He emphasized the importance of full-season availability for players in T20 leagues as it's unfair to fans, owners, and captains when players leave after reaching the final hurdle.
title: 'It's not fair': Akram slams England players for leaving IPL early

description: Gautam Gambhir praised Shah Rukh Khan as the best owner he's worked with, highlighting their non-cricket discussions. Under Gambhir’s mentorship, Kolkata Knight Riders have regained form this season. Despite past struggles, KKR topped the table. Gambhir credits their success to SRK’s trust and his own accountability. KKR face Sunrisers Hyderabad next in Qualifier 1.
title: 'He had never asked me a single question': Gambhir hails SRK

description: Young cricketers in Sopore, once dubbed 'chota Pakistan,' paused a match for record polling. Muazzin Manzoor, a first-time voter, highlighted the need for change. A groom in Nowshera voted before his wedding, and even an active Lashkar-e-Taiba militant's brother exercised his right to vote.
title: Families of active militants, youth root for democracy in Valley

description: RCB skipper Faf du Plessis shares insights on the team's IPL transformation, from early struggles to playoff contention. He discusses key players, strategic decisions, and the team's mindset heading into the Eliminator, highlighting the role of support staff and the importance of fielding, fitness, and teamwork. With the Eliminator against former champions Rajasthan Royals in Ahmedabad looming, the 39-year-old du Plessis believes the job is still only half done.
title: We were very hungry to turn it around: Faf du Plessis

description: Former Karnataka CM HD Kumaraswamy urges nephew Prajwal Revanna to return to India from Germany and cooperate with SIT in the sex scandal case, emphasizing family dignity and reputation preservation. Grandfather Deve Gowda's political legacy and JD(S) party's values add significance to the plea. The scandal involves allegations circulated on pen drives before Karnataka elections, highlighting the family's political involvement.
title: HD Kumaraswamy urges Prajwal Revanna to return to India

description: During testimony on Monday, Michael Cohen confessed to stealing $30,000 from Donald Trump by inflating expenses in his hush-money reimbursement. On his fourth day of cross-examination, Cohen was questioned about a significant part of a larger repayment he received for the $130,000 he paid to Stormy Daniels. This repayment included an additional $50,000 that Cohen claimed he paid to Red Finch, a technology company hired to improve Trump's ranking in a pre-election CNBC poll.
title: Trump trial turns chaotic as judge clears court, warns witness

description: Google releases white paper on Microsoft's security lapses to US government. Offers discounts to government agencies and corporate customers to switch to Google Workspace due to cybersecurity failures. Reportedly seen by Bloomberg, Google suggests a safer alternative to Microsoft Office. Alphabet-owned company offers discounts and incident response services from Mandiant security business.
title: Google highlights 'Microsoft's security failures' to the US government

description: India has become one of Asia's most active IPO markets this year, driven by a surge in smaller deals. This trend is shifting as larger share sales emerge, enhancing India's appeal to global investors who are reallocating funds amidst China's uneven recovery. Several factors contribute to this momentum, including record-high stock prices, robust economic growth, and earnings exceeding expectations.
title: Big IPOs seen making a comeback in India as stock boom continues

description: Women voters in West Bengal play a crucial role in elections, with parties offering schemes and freebies to attract them. Trinamool and BJP compete over the Lakshmir Bhandar scheme, while Congress-Left combine introduces the Mahalakshmi scheme.
title: Why all parties are courting women in Bengal

description: Delhi is facing a severe heatwave with a red alert from the IMD. Najafgarh recorded 47.4 degrees Celsius, Safdarjung 44.1. Mungeshpur, Pitampura, and Jafarpur also saw high temperatures. The forecast predicts temperatures reaching 46 degrees Celsius by Friday, coinciding with the Lok Sabha elections. The IMD advised staying indoors and keeping hydrated.
title: Red alert in Delhi: Extreme temperatures to stay till Friday

description: Mumbai Indians' 4 Indian T20 WC players spark IPL impact debate for Team India. KKR, SRH lack WC squad members. Rinku Singh, Yashasvi Jaiswal, and Virat Kohli's absence raise selection concerns. Uncertainty surrounds India reserves.
title: No India T20 World Cup player in top two IPL teams

description: Over 22,000 candidates qualified for the Telangana Engineering Common Entrance Test (ECET) for lateral entry into engineering programmes. Officials mentioned 10,800 seats eligible for fee reimbursement and an additional 14,000 vacant seats, totaling over 25,000 seats this year. Results were swiftly released, allowing ample time for career planning.
title: Hyd students left dejected as US visa slots vanish in a flash

description: CCS sleuths booked a case against M Nethaji and Sri Priyanka Enterprise after 537 victims reported being duped of Rs 206 crore in a scheme promising 15% annual interest.
title: Hyderabad businessman dupes investors of Rs 200 crore
K'taka high court: One pic doesn't tell a perfect marriage story
3 UP villages log 100% polling, cash pooled in to fly 1 from Bengaluru
‘Opposition will form govt, BJP’s falling everywhere’

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad and Kolkata Knight Riders, featuring Travis Head and Abhishek Sharma's explosive batting, will face off in an intense IPL match with Rahul Tripathi providing middle-order impetus.
title: Qualifier 1: Knight Riders, Sunrisers Hyderabad look to put on a show
ED to MHA: Probe AAP for Rs 7cr from foreign donors
Monk sues Bengal CM Mamata even as BSS distances itself from his remark
Cops seek trial of teen who ran over 2 as an adult

description: Gautam Gambhir discussed the IPL rivalry between Chennai Super Kings and Kolkata Knight Riders, highlighting similarities in strategies and approaches. The former left-hander went on to say that both sides' plans were extremely similar. KKR will play for a spot in the final when they take on Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH) in Qualifier 1 on Tuesday at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad.
title: 'The way MS Dhoni...': Gautam Gambhir opens up on KKR-CSK rivalry

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, who has been vocal against the Naveen Patnaik-led BJD govt on Ratna Bhandar (treasury) issue involving Puri Jagannath temple, enquired about the controversial matter from servitors while offering prayers in the shrine on Monday.
title: What is mystery behind Ratna Bhandar keys: PM says he will unravel it

description: Nagpurians to face typical summer after cool May. Adults show heat stroke symptoms like dizziness, rapid heartbeat. Fever in children, including infants, could be due to heat. Dehydration fever in newborns needs immediate attention. Dehydration in newborns requires expressed breast milk and may need hospitalization. Proper breathing, circulation, and cooling are key for treatment.
title: Fever in children could be due to heat stroke: Doctors
